{{Infobox anthem |title = {{transl|am|Wodefit Gesgeshi, Widd Innat Ityopp'ya}} |transcription = {{lang|am|የዜግነት ክብር}} |english_title = March Forward, Dear Mother Ethiopia |image = Emblem_of_Ethiopia.svg |prefix = National |country = {{ETH}} |author = Dereje Melaku Mengesha |lyrics_date = |composer = Solomon Lulu Mitiku |music_date = |adopted = 1992 |sound = Wedefit_Gesgeshi_Widd_Innat_Ittyoppya.ogg |sound_title = Wedefit Gesgeshi Widd Innat Ethiopia (Instrumental) }}
'''March Forward, Dear Mother Ethiopia''' ({{lang-am|የዜግነት ክብር}} ; [[File:Whedefit Gesgeshi Woude Henate Ethiopia (Title).png|250px|የዜግነት ክብር]] ; ''{{transl|am|Wodefit Gesgeshi, Widd Innat Ityopp'ya}}''<ref name="Ethanth">{{cite book|last1=Minahan|first1=James|title=The Complete Guide to National Symbols and Emblems [2 Volumes]|date=2009|publisher=ABC-CLIO|isbn=0313344973|page=830|url=https://www.google.com/books?id=jfrWCQAAQBAJ&pg=PA830|accessdate=17 November 2017}}</ref>) is the [[national anthem]] of the [[Federal Democratic Republic of Ethiopia]].
==History== The anthem's lyrics were written by Dereje Melaku Mengesha, and the music was composed by Solomon Lulu Mitiku. The song was adopted in 1992, as part of reforms that followed the dissolution of the [[Derg]] government.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://nationalanthems.me/ethiopia-wodefit-gesgeshi-widd-innat-ityoppya | title=Ethiopia: Wedefit Gesgeshi, Wid Enat Ityopya | publisher=NationalAnthems.me | accessdate=2011-08-11 }}</ref>
