{{EngvarB|date=April 2016}} {{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}} {{Infobox book | name = The Long Cosmos | author = [[Terry Pratchett]] & [[Stephen Baxter (author)|Stephen Baxter]] | language = English | country = United Kingdom | series = [[The Long Earth (series)|The Long Earth]] | genre = [[Science fiction]] novel | publisher = [[Penguin Random House]] | isbn = | <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Novels or Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books --> | title_orig = | translator = | image = | cover_artist = | release_date = 30 June 2016 | media_type = Print (hardcover) | pages = | preceded_by = [[The Long Utopia]] | followed_by = }} '''''The Long Cosmos''''' is a [[science fiction]] novel by [[Terry Pratchett]] and [[Stephen Baxter (author)|Stephen Baxter]] published on 30 June 2016.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.penguin.co.uk/books/1096263/the-long-cosmos/ | title=The Long Cosmos | publisher=DoubleDay | accessdate=20 April 2016}}</ref> It is the final [[Serial (literature)|installment]] in the award-winning five-book [[Parallel universe (fiction)|parallel-Earth]] series ''[[The Long Earth (series)|The Long Earth]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theguardian.com/books/2016/jun/24/the-long-cosmos-by-terry-pratchett-and-stephen-baxter|title=The Long Cosmos by Terry Pratchett and Stephen Baxter – a final farewell to the Long Earth|author=Jenny Colgan|date=24 June 2016|work=the Guardian|accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref>
It is the second book in the series published [[List of works published posthumously|posthumously]] from Terry Pratchett.
==Plot== '''''The Long Cosmos''''' further follows the adventures of Joshua Valienté and Lobsang.
